Bothriochloa insculpta

    Authority   (A. Rich) A. Camus
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3786

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A hardy, stoloniferous grass growing 30-100 cm high.
   Leaves, stems and seed-heads are aromatic. USES Used for pasture but
   should not be grazed to heavily. Can also be used for hay before it
   becomes stemmy. KILLING T Has some winter hardiness. GROWING PERIOD
   Summer-growing perennial grass. COMMON NAMES Sweet-pitted grass,
   Pinhole grass, Stippel grass, Creeping blue grass. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Amphilophis insculpta. In the equatorial zone
   Sweet-pitted grass can be found at elevations between 1000-2000 m,
   further north and south it can be found at elevations between sea level
   and 2000 m. It is common in open bush and grassland, mainly in heavy
   textured black soils. An annual burn is necessary if grazing is not
   heavy.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 50 [RAIN, TEXT, DRA]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 184 [USE]
